  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops with Wi-Fi in San Francisco for evening work?",
  "response": "San Francisco is home to numerous coffee shops with great Wi-Fi, perfect for evening work. Here are some top recommendations:\n\n1. **Sightglass Coffee**\n   - **Location**: 270 7th St, San Francisco, CA 94103\n   - **Hours**: Open until 7 PM\n   - **Features**: Known for its spacious and industrial-chic atmosphere, Sightglass offers reliable Wi-Fi and plenty of seating, making it ideal for evening work.\n\n2. **Philz Coffee**\n   - **Location**: Multiple locations, including 3101 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110\n   - **Hours**: Many locations open until 8 PM\n   - **Features**: Philz is famous for its customizable coffee blends and cozy atmosphere. It's a great spot for settling in with your laptop for a few hours.\n\n3. **The Mill**\n   - **Location**: 736 Divisadero St, San Francisco, CA 94117\n   - **Hours**: Open until 8 PM\n   - **Features**: The Mill is perfect for those seeking a hip and comfortable environment. It offers strong Wi-Fi and is known for its delicious baked goods.\n\n4. **Blue Bottle Coffee**\n   - **Location**: Multiple locations, including 66 Mint St, San Francisco, CA 94103\n   - **Hours**: Some locations open until 7 PM\n   - **Features**: Blue Bottle is renowned for its high-quality coffee and minimalist design. The reliable Wi-Fi and quiet atmosphere make it a good choice for focused work.\n\n5. **Four Barrel Coffee**\n   - **Location**: 375 Valencia St, San Francisco, CA 94103\n   - **Hours**: Open until 8 PM\n   - **Features**: Four Barrel has a laid-back vibe and excellent Wi-Fi. It's a popular spot among freelancers and students.\n\nThese coffee shops provide a comfortable and conducive environment for evening work, with reliable Wi-Fi to keep you connected. Enjoy your productive evening in San Francisco!",
